declarations.comments: Increases the indentation level by one indent.
declarations.title: indent

declarations.comments: Increases the indentation level by the number of spaces (for alignment purposes).
declarations.title: align

declarations.comments: Increases the indentation level so that it aligns to the current column.
declarations.title: alignCurrentColumn

declarations.comments:
Adds an annotation to a document. Printers can interpret annotations to style
their output, eg. ANSI colors.
declarations.title: annotate

declarations.comments: Build a document based on the current layout position.
declarations.title: withPosition

declarations.comments:
The most basic document leaf. This should not contain newlines. If it does
your document will look very funny.
declarations.title: text

declarations.comments: Inserts a hard line break.
declarations.title: break

declarations.comments: Inserts a space when in a flex group, otherwise inserts a break.
declarations.title: spaceBreak

declarations.comments: Inserts nothing when in a flex group, otherwise inserts a break.
declarations.title: softBreak

declarations.comments: A singe space character.
declarations.title: space

declarations.comments: Appends documents with a break in between them.
declarations.title: lines

declarations.comments: Appends documents with a space in between them.
declarations.title: words

declarations.comments: Appends two documents with a break between them.
declarations.title: appendBreak

declarations.comments: Appends two documents with a space between them.
declarations.title: appendSpace

declarations.comments:
Appends two documents with a space between them, falling back to a
break if that does not fit.
declarations.title: appendSpaceBreak

declarations.comments:
Attempts to layout the first document when in a flex group, falling back
to the second as a default.
declarations.title: flexAlt

declarations.comments:
Attempts to layout the document with flex alternatives, falling back
to defaults if it doesn't fit the page width.
declarations.title: flexGroup

declarations.comments:
Attempts to layout the first document with flex alternatives, falling
back to defaults if it doesn't fit the page width. If the flex alternatives
are used then the second document will be appended, otherwise the third
document will be appended.
declarations.title: flexSelect

declarations.comments: Appends documents with a space-break in between them.
declarations.title: paragraph

declarations.comments:
Constructs a wrapping paragraph from a blob of text. Ignores newlines and
multiple spaces.
declarations.title: textParagraph

declarations.comments:
Uses an opening and closing document to wrap another document.
```purescript
example = enclose (text "(") (text ")") (text "inner")
```
declarations.title: enclose

declarations.comments:
Uses an opening and closing document to wrap another document, falling
back when the inner document is empty.
```purescript
example = encloseEmptyAlt (text "[ ") (text " ]") (text "[]") mempty
```
declarations.title: encloseEmptyAlt

declarations.comments:
Uses an opening and closing document, as a well as a separator, to render
a series of documents.
```purescript`
example = encloseWithSeparator (text "[") (text "]") (",") [ text "one", text "two" ]
```
declarations.title: encloseWithSeparator

declarations.comments: Appends a series of documents together with a separator in between them.
declarations.title: foldWithSeparator

declarations.comments:
Appends a series of documents together with a given append function. This
is notable because it ignores empty documents.
declarations.title: foldWith

declarations.comments:
*EXPERIMENTAL:* modifies printing state and options locally for a document.
This may change or be removed at any time.
declarations.title: locally

declarations.comments:
*EXPERIMENTAL:* modifies printing state and options locally for a document.
This may change or be removed at any time. Differs from `locally` in that the
document can be responsive to options.
declarations.title: withLocalOptions

declarations.comments:
Prints a documents given a printer and print options.

```purescript
print plainText twoSpaces myDoc
```

This will use full line-lookahead from the start of a flex group. If it
encounters a break or content overflows the page-width, it will layout
the group using flex alternative defaults instead.
declarations.title: print

declarations.comments:
Custom printers can be used to render richer documents than just plain
text.
* `emptyBuffer` - The initial buffer.
* `writeText` - Should write a string with the given width to the buffer.
* `writeIndent` - Should write indentation with the given width to the buffer.
* `writeBreak` - Should write a line break to the buffer.
* `enterAnnotation` - Called when entering a new annotated region. Provides the full annotation stack.
* `leaveAnnotation` - Called when leaving an annotated region. Provides the full annotation stack.
* `flushBuffer` - Called at the end of the document to get the final result.
declarations.title: Printer

declarations.comments: A plain text printer. Can be used with any document.
declarations.title: plainText

declarations.comments:
Configuration options for the printer.
* `pageWidth` - The printer will try not to exceed this width on any given line.
* `ribbonRatio` - Ratio between 0.0 and 1.0, defaults to 1.0. The printer will
  use this ratio to calculate the printable area between the current indentation
  level and the `pageWidth`.
* `indentUnit` - The string used for a single indent.
* `indentWidth` - The assumed character width of a single `indentUnit`.
declarations.title: PrintOptions

declarations.comments: Prints 2-space indents, with a default 80-column page width.
declarations.title: twoSpaces

declarations.comments: Prints 4-space indents, with a default 120-column page width.
declarations.title: fourSpaces

declarations.comments: Prints tab indents (4-wide), with a default 120-column page width.
declarations.title: tabs

declarations.comments: Document lines and columns are 0-based offsets.
declarations.title: Position

declarations.comments:
Documents are built using `<>` as horizontal, line-wise concatenation.
The functions in this module let you build documents that respond well
to width constraints (such as `flexGroup` and `flexAlt`).
declarations.title: Doc

declarations.comments: Only applies the provided function if the document is non-empty.
declarations.title: notEmpty

declarations.comments: Checks whether the document is empty.
declarations.title: isEmpty

declarations.comments:
Only applies the provided function if both documents are
non-empty, otherwise just yields whichever is non-empty.
declarations.title: bothNotEmpty

modules.comments:
This module provides functions printing with cascading ANSI styles.
ANSI annotations closer to the root will cascade down to child nodes,
where styles closer to the leaves take precedence. Indentation is
never printed with ANSI styles, only the text elements of the document.

declarations.comments: Prints a document with a specific background color.
declarations.title: background

declarations.comments: Prints a document with bold styling.
declarations.title: bold

declarations.comments: Prints a document with dim styling.
declarations.title: dim

declarations.comments: Prints a document with a specific foreground color.
declarations.title: foreground

declarations.comments: Prints a document with inverse styling.
declarations.title: inverse

declarations.comments: Prints a document with italic styling.
declarations.title: italic

declarations.comments:
Resets all cascading styles for a document so that outer styles won't
interfere with inner styles.
declarations.title: reset

declarations.comments: Prints a document with strikethrough styling.
declarations.title: strikethrough

declarations.comments: Prints a document with underline styling.
declarations.title: underline

modules.name: Dodo.Ansi

declarations.comments:
A graphics parameter, controls how text appears; for example, bold,
underlined, foreground color, background color.
declarations.title: GraphicsParam

declarations.comments: The standard set of 16 ANSI colors.
declarations.title: Color

declarations.comments:
Unlike `Doc`s, which can only be joined along a line, `DocBox`es
are two-dimensional units which can be stacked vertically and
horizontally (eg. for tables).

`Doc`s can be lifted into `DocBox` by using the `doxBox` printer.
```purescript
example = Dodo.print docBox twoSpaces myDoc
````
declarations.title: DocBox

declarations.comments: A newtype whose Semigroup instance stacks DocBoxes vertically.
declarations.title: Vertical

declarations.comments: A newtype whose Semigroup instance stacks DocBoxes horizontally.
declarations.title: Horizontal

declarations.comments:
Pads a DocBox vertically to fit the tallest box within a
horizontal run.
```purescript
example =
  valign Middle shortDoc
    `happend` tallDoc
```
declarations.title: valign

declarations.comments:
Pads a DocBox horizontally to fit the widest line within a
vertical run.
```purescript
example =
  halign Middle skinnyDoc
    `vappend` wideDoc
```
declarations.title: halign

declarations.comments: Joins two DocBoxes vertically on top of each other.
declarations.title: vappend

declarations.comments: Joins two DocBoxes horizontally next to each other.
declarations.title: happend

declarations.comments: Joins DocBoxes in a vertical run.
declarations.title: vertical

declarations.comments: Joins DocBoxes in a vertical run with uniform horizontal alignment.
declarations.title: verticalWithAlign

declarations.comments: Joins DocBoxes in a horizontal run.
declarations.title: horizontal

declarations.comments: Joins DocBoxes in a horizontal run with uniform vertical alignment.
declarations.title: horizontalWithAlign

declarations.comments:
Resizes a box to a larger or equivalent size, positioning its content
according to its alignment.
declarations.title: resize

declarations.comments:
Fills a box to a given size with a Doc. The Doc is assumed
to be 1x1. Providing a Doc of a different size will result
in incorrect layouts.
```
example =
  fill (Ansi.dim (Dodo.text "-"))
    { width: 100
    , height: 1
    }
```
declarations.title: fill

declarations.comments: Vertical padding of a specific height.
declarations.title: vpadding

declarations.comments: Horizontal padding of a specific width.
declarations.title: hpadding

declarations.comments: Returns the size of a DocBox.
declarations.title: sizeOf

declarations.comments: Checks whether a DocBox is empty.
declarations.title: isEmpty

declarations.comments: The identity DocBox.
declarations.title: empty

declarations.comments: Converts a DocBox back into Doc for printing.
declarations.title: toDoc

declarations.comments:
A printer which can lift a Doc into DocBox. It is assumed that
the Doc's annotations respect a distributive law:
``` purescript
annotate ann (a <> b) = annotate ann a <> annotate ann b
````
declarations.title: docBox
